      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Letting go means accepting that you cannot force the past back into your life, even if it feels like a hollow space. The crushing weight you feel is a natural response to loss, but trying to fill it with noise or routine only adds more pressure to a broken foundation. You are not obligated to stay in a house that no longer fits, so consider that walking away might be the only way to finally stop carrying this burden.",
